67 poi, come inebrïate da li odori, 68 riprofondavan sé nel miro gurge, 69 e s’una intrava, un’altra n’uscia fori.

query.result:
**English:**
64 From this river issued living sparks, 65 and on every side they settled on the flowers, 66 like rubies set in gold;
