query.result:
**English:**
70 “The high desire that inflames and urges you 71 to have knowledge of what you will see, 72 pleases me all the more the more it swells;
73 but it is necessary that you drink of this water 74 before such thirst is quenched in you”: 75 thus spoke to me the sun of my eyes.
**Cornish:**
